The paper deals with the problem of constructing explicit hitting sets for Combinatorial Shapes, which are a class of statistical tests. This problem is related to computational complexity (cs.CC) as hitting sets are often used in complexity theory to prove lower bounds. The paper also involves the construction of perfect hash families and hitting sets for combinatorial rectangles, which are topics in data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper involves combinatorial analysis (cs.CR) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM) in the study of Combinatorial Shapes.
